      <h2>1. Prefatory Observations & Preamble</h2>
      <p class="large-block">By accessing or using DocuWrite Pro ("Platform"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree, please discontinue use immediately. These Terms establish the mutual rights and responsibilities between the Platform and its Users, setting the foundation for lawful and respectful engagement.</p>

      <h2>2. Definitions & Interpretive Maxims</h2>
      <p><strong>Definitions:</strong> "Services" refers to document editing, exporting, and related features. "User Content" means any material you provide. "Third-Party Services" are external integrations not controlled by us.</p>
      <p><strong>Interpretation:</strong> Headings are for clarity only. Words in singular include plural, and vice versa. All obligations shall be interpreted in good faith with due regard to industry standards.</p>

      <h2>3. Scope of Services & Execution Prerogatives</h2>
      <p>DocuWrite Pro provides document creation, manipulation, and sharing features. We reserve the right to update, change, or discontinue features at any time without notice, while striving to maintain overall service stability.</p>

      <h2>4. Cookies, Identifiers & Advertising</h2>
      <p>Our hosting and integrated services may use cookies and similar identifiers. Advertisements may appear and can be tailored based on context or external providers. You may manage preferences in your browser settings.</p>

      <h2>5. Code Execution & File Access</h2>
      <p>With your consent, DocuWrite Pro may interact with files on your device for processing (e.g., uploads, exports). All execution remains within your browser’s permissions and is never performed without authorization.</p>

      <h2>6. Data Collection & Telemetry</h2>
      <p>We may collect diagnostic and performance data to improve services, including error reports and feature usage statistics. Such data is handled in accordance with applicable privacy standards.</p>

      <h2>7. User Content & Licence</h2>
      <p>By providing content, you grant us a licence to use it for delivering services and improvements. You remain the owner of your content, and this licence is limited to functional and operational needs.</p>

      <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We are not responsible for third-party services or content accessed through DocuWrite Pro. Review their policies separately before engaging with their services.</p>

      <h2>9. Availability & Termination</h2>
      <p>We may suspend or terminate services at any time. Users are responsible for maintaining backups of their work. Service interruptions may occur due to maintenance or unforeseen circumstances.</p>

      <h2>10. Security & Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable steps to protect data but cannot guarantee absolute security. You are responsible for safe use of downloads and shared content, particularly when interacting with external platforms.</p>

      <h2>11. Warranties & Limitations</h2>
